						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar lying by the road-side of the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1403, Plava, Vaiśākha śu. 15, Thursday = 1481 A.D., April 14. The weekday was Saturday.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the grant of lands for the Dēva Brāhmaṇas and as <hi rend="italic">bhaṭa-vṛitti</hi> to the <hi rend="italic">karaṇika</hi> by Śrī Mīnugu Malla at Cherlōguḍipāḍu in Guriṁdāla-sīma which belonged to his <hi rend="italic">nāyaṁkara,</hi> for the merit of his grandfather Chānnēniṁgāru, father Chitnēniṁgāru and uncle Koṁḍamanāyaniṁgāru. </p>						

						</summary>
